  "prompt": "What happened to the other Jedi that survived Order 66? How effective was the purge?",
  "response": "Order 66 was devastating for the Jedi Order. While many Jedi were killed during the initial purge, some did survive through various means:\n\n1. Some Jedi survived by hiding or going into exile, such as:\n- Obi-Wan Kenobi\n- Yoda\n- Ahsoka Tano\n- Kanan Jarrus\n- Cal Kestis\n\n2. The effectiveness of the purge was significant:\n- Approximately 99% of the Jedi were killed\n- Most Jedi were caught off-guard by clone troopers turning against them\n- The Jedi Temple was attacked and many Jedi were killed, including younglings\n\n3. Surviving Jedi often:\n- Went into hiding\n- Changed their identities\n- Avoided using the Force\n- Tried to protect themselves and potentially other Force-sensitive individuals\n\n4. Some survivors were eventually hunted down by Darth Vader and the Inquisitors in the years following Order 66\n\nWhile the purge was extremely effective in decimating the Jedi Order, a small number of Jedi managed to survive and continue the legacy of the Jedi in secret during the early years of the Galactic Empire.",
